  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "SALES MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>Sales Manager Responsibilities:</p><ul><li>Supervising and guiding the sales team as well as providing incentives to motivate staff to achieve sales targets.</li><li>Assist with the sales process by maintaining a fully stocked store.</li><li>Maintain an up-to-date knowledge of product features and sales promotion</li><li>Continually meeting or exceeding sales quotas.</li><li>Monitoring the performance of the sales team.</li><li>Ensuring that the store is clean and well-maintained at all times.</li><li>Building and maintaining good working relationships with customers.</li><li>Identifying opportunities and strategies to increase sales.</li><li>Regularly attending sales meetings and training sessions.</li><li>Ensuring that the store is adequately stocked with company products.</li><li>Performing all duties of the Sales Manager in cases of absence or emergency.</li><li>Updates managers by consolidating, analysing, and forwarding daily action summaries.</li><li>Recommend and display items that match customer needs.</li><li>Manage point-of-sale processes.</li><li>Tracks sales expenses by tracking, consolidating, analysing, and summarising expenses, and forwarding for reimbursement.</li><li>Update customer records in the company database as required</li><li>Perform any other duties assigned by the director.</li></ul><p>Sales Assistant Manager Requirements:</p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Hotel Management</li><li>Proven experience in sales and customer service.</li><li>Proficient in all Microsoft Office applications.</li><li>The ability to work in a fast-paced environment.</li><li>Excellent problem-solving skills.</li><li>Strong management and leadership skills.</li><li>Effective communication skills.</li><li>Exceptional customer service skills.</li><li>The Ability to multitask and work under pressure.</li><li>Availability to work within opening hours (e.g. evenings, holidays, weekends).</li><li>The ability to work under pressure.</li></ul>",
